com.mindfusion.scheduling.model

Interface ScheduleListener

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ChangeListener, java.util.EventListener

    public interface ScheduleListener
extends ChangeListener
    Defines the events raised by the Schedule class.

      • recurrenceReset

        void recurrenceReset(ItemEvent e)
        Description copied from interface: ScheduleListener
        Raised when the recurrence pattern associated with an item has been reset, causing all associated exception items to be lost.

        The recurrence is reset when the value of any of the properties that define it is changed. The recurrence is also reset when it is associated to or dissociated from an item.

        Parameters:
        e - An ItemEvent object.

      • instantiateItem

        void instantiateItem(InstantiateItemEvent e)
        Description copied from interface: ScheduleListener
        Raised when deserializing a custom item whose type has not been registered.

        This event is being raised during deserialization for all custom items whose types have not been previously registered within the system through a call to Schedule.registerItemClass(java.lang.Class<? extends com.mindfusion.scheduling.model.Item>, java.lang.String, int). The event provides an alternative way for instantiating item of custom types.

        Parameters:
        e - An InstantiateItemEvent object.

      • instantiateResource

        void instantiateResource(InstantiateResourceEvent e)
        Description copied from interface: ScheduleListener
        Raised when deserializing a custom resource whose type has not been registered.

        This event is being raised during deserialization for all custom resources whose types have not been previously registered within the system through a call to Schedule.registerResourceClass(java.lang.Class<? extends com.mindfusion.scheduling.model.Resource>, java.lang.String, int). The event provides an alternative way for instantiating resources of custom types.

        Parameters:
        e - An InstantiateResourceEvent object.

      • serializeTag

        void serializeTag(SerializeTagEvent e)
        Description copied from interface: ScheduleListener
        Raised during XML serialization to enable users to perform custom serialization of the tag values of items and resources.

        This event is being raised during the serialization of item and resource tag values in a XML document. If the event is not handled the system will try to serialize the tags as an arbitrary objects.

        Parameters:
        e - A SerializeTagEvent object.
